title: Eyes on the Surprise
description: When David ruins Vivie's big surprise, Barney helps David work on thinking before acting with a game of Jungle Hide-and-Seek. David realizes that controlling excitable impulses is challenging, but possible!

title: Time and Time Again/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/May the Best Taz Win
description: Time and Time Again: The babies learn the importance of telling time./May the Best Taz Win: Lola learns she can't be the best at every sport.

title: Santa's Toyshop
description: After a hot cocoa disaster, Santa Claus hires The Looney Builders to build him a new toyshop in time to save Christmas.

title: The Creature from the Chocolate Chip/The Looney Riddle (song)/Card Bored Box
description: Creature from the Chocolate Chip: Sylvester eats all of Granny's cookies then makes up a cookie monster to blame./Card Bored Box: Faced with nothing to do, the babies use a cardboard box and their imaginations to make playtime fun.

title: Carnaval
description: Carina Capybara hires The Looney Builders to build her Samba School a float for Brazil's Carnaval parade. She soon realizes the float will be even better if they incorporate her students' ideas, and they all work together to revise the design.

title: Bat-Blast-Off!
description: When King Tut steals an ancient artifact that makes his Carcophagus magically fast, MOE equips Bam with rocket boosters to catch the villain and Bam must learn how to control all that speed.

title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

title: Thomas' Promise
description: When Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the same load to Whiff's Recycling Plant, Thomas suggests they each take half of the load, but Diesel turns it into a race.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Bat-Buds Forever
description: Bibi and Batwing must work together to get past the Legion of Zoom in order to deliver a new giant screen to Batcomputer.

title: Polar Plunge
description: Pro snowboarder Pepper Polar Bear hires The Looney Builders to build a ski resort. Pepper soon learns that others have different skill levels.

title: Robo-Runner
description: The Looney Builders are hired to build a festive course for the Fall foot race. Wile E. Coyote is determined to beat the Road Runner with his Robo-Runner despite its malfunctions.

title: Trash to Treasure
description: When David worries about how much trash is created by their lunch, Barney makes a game of Reducing, Reusing and Recycling. After making cleaning up fun, Barney inspires the whole community to contribute and care as much as the kids do.

title: Forever and Always
description: Vivie fears she's jeopardized Nonna's love after she accidentally knocks over Nonna's flower pots. During an adventure in the Enchanted Garden, Barney's big mistakes ruin their fun and Vivie realizes the power of unconditional love.

title: The Pizza Extravaganza
description: Nonna's chronic ankle injury puts her annual Pizza Extravaganza at risk of not happening. Vivie discovers that with the help and care of their community, she and Nonna will be able to manage anything!

title: Banebuggy
description: The Batwheels take on a new vehicular villain who keeps growing bigger and bigger while learning that size doesn't always win the day.

title: Cat-Taz-Trophy/If You're Looney (song)/Duck! Monster! Duck!
description: Cat-Taz-Trophy: Sylvester and Taz team up to win a toy racecar derby./Duck! Monster! Duck!: Daffy reads the babies a scary story, only to end up frightening himself.

title: Flush Hour/Paws and Feathers (song)/I Strain
description: Flush Hour: The babies learn the purpose of toilets./I Strain: Petunia gets hooked on watching television and stops playing with her friends.

title: School Daze/Mary Had a Baby Duck (song)/Things That Go Bugs in the Night
description: School Daze: The babies play pretend school in preparation for the real thing./Things That Go Bugs in the Night: Bugs must find the courage to discover what's making scary noises outside.

title: Taz in Toyland/Born to Sing (song)/A Secret Tweet
description: Taz in Toyland: After Taz breaks all of his toys, Granny gives him one last chance to care for something./A Secret Tweet: The babies plan a surprise birthday party for Tweety.

title: Mamma Mia Pizzeria
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Giovanna Badgerini to update her family's pizzeria in Italy. However, Giovanna's Mamma prefers the old way of doing things, which causes setbacks with the build until the crew helps them compromise.

title: A Work of Parts
description: Grady fills a big crack in the park's entryway with concrete so no one trips. Vivie comes up with the idea to add found items, creating a beautiful art piece and discovers that even though she's small she can have a big effect on the park.

title: The Good Apology
description: Mel doesn't quite understand the value of a sincere apology after nearly damaging David's special toy. A big mishap from Billy and Baby Bop makes her understand the value of saying you're sorry, and meaning it.

title: It's a Jungle Out There
description: While on an Enchanted Jungle trek, David loses the friends' magical explorer mobile, after promising to remember where they parked it. Barney helps David learn it's okay to make mistakes and the responsible thing to do is try to fix them.

title: Pauleen's Pins
description: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build an ice bowling alley in Looneyburg. Her homesickness causes setbacks until the crew helps her feel better.

title: Bruce Bunny/Baby Bunny (song)/Leader of the Pack
description: Bruce Bunny: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce./Leader of the Pack: Daffy starts a secret password club for everyone except Bugs.

title: Grandpa Oink
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Petunia's Grandpa Oink to upgrade his farm. They take things too far and Grandpa Oink misses some of the things he loves most about farming.

title: Hare Ball
description: Marvin the Martian hires The Looney Builders to build an outer space ball court on Mars. Bugs is a big fan of the sport, and soon becomes a ball and build "hog."

title: Sam's Stylin' Salon
description: Sam Sheepdog hires The Looney Builders to build him a salon. Sam offers his custom cut only to learn that different folks want different styles.

title: Porky Perfect Parade
description: The Looney Builders build a float to lead the Flower Parade, but Porky won't settle for anything less than Porky Perfect.

title: Father's Day Road Trip
description: When Mel and her dad's Father's Day road trip gets cancelled, Mel ends up taking him on an imaginary trip instead so they can still spend time together. Barney adds magic to create a fun and special Father's Day journey to remember.

title: Baby Bop Blues
description: Baby Bop keeps having meltdowns during a game with the kids, making it hard for everyone to play together. Barney steps in to figure out what is causing Baby Bop's upsets and helps her manage them so everyone can continue to have fun.

title: Rainy Day
description: When it starts to rain outside, Porky hopes to show The Looney Builders that they can still have fun inside by building a fort.

title: Bugs and the Beanstalk
description: The Looney Builders build a castle for Elmer the Giant. They admire his toys and use them without his permission.

title: All Mechas on Deck/Where There's A Wheel, There's A Way
description: Lloyd's testing a wind-up powered go-cart, but a problem arises when it keeps running out of energy./Sif's coming in for a landing at the rocket launch site - until her rocket is pushed off course by a satellite!

title: Prizeworthy Birdie
description: Sunny Seagull hires The Looney Builders to build a carnival on Looneyburg's pier. The crew gets so caught up trying to win the games that they lose sight of what matters.

title: Cake Bake
description: The Looney Builders take turns distracting Petunia as they build her a big surprise birthday cake in the backyard.

title: Spiffledipped
description: While Green Lantern is having his spaceship repaired in the Batcave, the Batwheels want to play with his adorable alien pet, only to discover that this cute critter has wild alien powers!

title: Too Far
description: When Baby Bop's playful teasing starts bothering Mel, Barney arranges a trip to the Castleverse where their adventure motivates Mel to finally speak up for herself.

title: Spin Out/Taz's Fridge (song)/Snow Day
description: Spinout: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy./Snow Day: The babies experience their first snowfall.

title: Nonna on the Move
description: When a day of fun with Nonna prompts Vivie to realize Nonna's declining mobility, Nonna and Barney help Vivie discover how she can care for Nonna by making simple adjustments that allow them to keep having fun in a slightly different way.

title: Finders Not Keepers
description: When Mel discovers the sunglasses she found belong to Grady, she still wants to keep them. Barney creates a high-seas adventure, where Mel realizes she's acting like a pirate taking what doesn't belong to her and returns the glasses.

title: Takers Keepers/D-A-F-F-Y (song)/To Tell the Tooth
description: Takers Keepers: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want./To Tell the Tooth: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

title: Someone's Missing
description: When David's cold keeps him stuck inside, Barney, Mel, and Vivie get creative and try to find a way to engage and have fun with their friend from the other side of the window.

title: Back on Board
description: Mel loses her confidence in skateboarding after a fall. Barney takes the kids on a trip on a high-seas adventure, where a stormy sea presents challenges that help Mel discover what she needs to feel safe trying new things again.

title: Big Energy Billy
description: Billy's big, boisterous energy causes accidental destruction during the kids' farm-play. Barney and the kids help him re-channel his exuberant strength more productively so they can all enjoy playing together.

title: Flight of the Kitty
description: Now that Catwoman has equipped Kitty with wings, Batwing tries to teach the easily-distracted Kitty how to fly.

title: Beignet Day
description: Zaida Gator hires The Looney Builders to build her a boat so she can share her beignets in the swamp. She soon realizes there are others to share with elsewhere and enlists the crew to make it possible.

title: Fire Fighters
description: The Looney Builders are hired by the town's volunteer firefighters to build a fire truck. Duty calls and they build on the go as they make rescues throughout Looneyburg.

title: Barney's Birthday
description: The kids are making a quilt for Barney's birthday featuring their favorite things to do with Barney. David has a hard time choosing just one thing, so Baby Bop and Billy help him decide just in time for the party.

title: Baseball Bunnies
description: The Looney Builders build a baseball field, but both Bugs and Lola want to be the pitcher for the big game later. They attempt to prove themselves as they work, causing setbacks with the build.

title: Looney Games
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Mayor Leghorn to build the venue for the Looney Games. They soon become overwhelmed by the job and must ask for help.

title: Lights Out
description: When a blackout upends Vivie's evening plans, Barney helps the kids pivot to night games and a campout. The night is made even more special by friends in the community, who come together and make the best out of the unexpected event.

title: Bibi and the Bad Seed
description: When Poison Ivy uses a rare pollen-spewing flower to put all of Gotham to sleep, it's up to Bibi to save her friends and save the day.

title: Puppet Showstopper
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Parth Peacock to build a puppet stage and puppets in India. They soon learn that Parth's form of puppetry differs from their own and must correct everything in time for his big show.

title: The Wizard of Bats
description: Bibi enters the world of The Wizard of Oz, where she meets familiar vehicle friends and goes on an amazing quest to see the wizard himself!

title: Coconut Hut
description: While on vacation, The Looney Builders befriend Coco the Crab and offer to build her a mini-resort. They shrink down for a micro-build and must rely on the island's natural resources to get the job done.

title: One More Game
description: When David wants to play video games all day, Barney puts a magical spin on some physical play that brings all the kids together in a game. David realizes the value of balancing both kinds of fun.

title: Cuckoo Cuckoo
description: Curt Cuckoo hires The Looney Builders to build a giant cuckoo clock in Germany to signal the start of Martinstag. The crew struggles to get it right until they ask Curt for his help.

title: Just My Style
description: Vivie is disappointed that the park's Splash Pad is closed. Barney creates a trip to the Castleverse and Mel is confused when Vivie isn't having fun doing all the things Mel is doing. Mel realizes that it's okay to have different interests.

title: Flower Power/Looney Tunes Zoo (song)/Lightning Bugs Sylvester
description: Flower Power: The babies all want to pick the best flowers for Granny but they end up destroying her garden./Lightning Bugs Sylvester: Sylvester learns to overcome his fear of lightning.

title: The Brighter Side
description: When Mel is in a pessimistic funk, Barney takes the kids on a trip to the Enchanted Barneyverse to help an optimistic fairy with an injured wing. Mel learns how to adopt an optimistic mindset to overcome adversity and help the fairy.

title: Condiment Chaos!
description: Condiment King takes advantage of no Batwheels being on patrol to unleash a barrage of ketchup and mustard on an unsuspecting Gotham.

title: Balloon Voyage
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Mac Gopher to build a hot air balloon for him and Tosh to ride in for a festival. Tosh keeps his fear of flying to himself and tries to weigh down the build to avoid liftoff.

title: Surf's Up
description: The Looney Builders are hired to build a surfside hangout in Australia for a surfing competition. Bugs and Daffy want to compete but are a little out of their league until Taz offers to teach them.

title: Just Like Liam
description: When David insists on copying everything Liam does, Barney takes the kids a trip to the Castleverse. They help Billy use his unique traits as a knight, leading David to the realization that it's important to be your unique self.

title: Pumpkin Panic
description: On Halloween Night, Poison Ivy brings all the pumpkins to life, creating an army of Snack-O-Lanterns that eat all the candy. It's up to Redbird and Bam to end her pumpkin panic to save Gotham's Halloween fun, as well as their own.

title: A Lot Like Lola/Baby Elmer Had a Friend (song)/Mother's Day Madness
description: A Lot Like Lola: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her./Mother's Day Madness: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

title: Mine!/Over the Burrow (song)/Sylvester the Pester
description: Mine!: Daffy learns a lesson in doing the right thing when he finds a purse filled with money./Sylvester the Pester: An attention-starved Sylvester won't let Granny have any time to herself.

title: The Great Christmas Caper
description: When Santa's sleigh is damaged, the Batwheels must help Santa deliver presents to the children of Gotham, and stop the Legion of Zoom from trying to steal them!

title: Comfort Level/Twinkle Baby Looney Star (song)/Like a Duck to Water
description: Comfort Level: Sylvester learns to live without his blankey./Like a Duck to Water: Daffy overcomes his fear of the swimming pool.

title: Dodo's Wacky Funhouse
description: Yoyo Dodo hires The Looney Builders to build a funhouse for Looneyburg. The crew thinks he's goofing around as they work, but soon discover they've misunderstood what Yoyo really wants.

title: Time to Try
description: At lunch in the park, Mel's friends are unwilling to try a taste of her kimchi. Barney whips up a beach day with Baby Bop, where she doesn't want to do anything new. The kids realize the value of trying new things to show others you care.

title: The Snuzzleberry Snatcher
description: Vivie gets frustrated when her soccer ball is popped by a cactus. Barney takes the kids on an enchanted garden adventure where Vivie learns that some plants in nature are pokey for protection.

title: Every Little Thing
description: The kids notice Grady is sad and Barney shows them that simple acts of kindness go a long way. Barney adds a dash of magic to the kids' actions that inspire others, allowing everyone to see the magnitude and power of simple acts of kindness.

title: It Takes Three
description: When Baby Bop feels left out of the kids game, she tries everything to be included. Barney uses fun, magic and empathy to help her understand that if you can't do what you want, the best thing is to find something else to enjoy.

title: Roller Disco
description: Pete Puma hires The Looney Builders to build a roller disco for Looneyburg. Lola is new to roller skating, but doesn't want to take it slow and practice.

title: The Bestah Way
description: When Harley Quinn's Hyena goes missing, Bibi agrees to help Jestah look for her.

title: Miss Prissy's Market
description: Miss Prissy hires The Looney Builders to build a grocery store for Looneyburg. When she stocks the store in unexpected ways, the crew must help her properly organize it.

title: MOE Alone
description: A sneaky trick strands the Batwheels at the docks, clearing the way for a Batcave heist by the Legion of Zoom. It's up to MOE to stop the Zoomers with zany improvised tricks and traps with a little help from Ace and Batcomputer.

title: Everyday Mother's Day
description: David and Liam want to do something special for their mom for an early Mother's Day. Barney helps them discover how to be observant of what others need, and how caring for their baby sister so mom can truly relax is the best gift of all.

title: Thomas Blasts Off
description: It's rocket launch day and all the trains get to help deliver the big rocket parts, but when Thomas is assigned a tiny part, he puts it off to help the others with their more exciting parts, not realizing that his "small" task was just as important.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Coaster Contest
description: The Looney Builders are hired to build a rollercoaster for Looneyburg. Bugs and Daffy soon get caught up trying to prove their part of the coaster is the best.

title: Shadow of a Doubt/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Christmas in July
description: Shadow of a Doubt: Tweety sheds some light on what a shadow is./Christmas in July: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

title: Jazz Hooves
description: Fosse Ferret hires The Looney Builders to build a stage for the kids' dance recital. Eggbert has stage fright, but Porky is determined to help him overcome it.

title: Yosemite Sam's Dude Ranch
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Yosemite Sam to build a dude ranch. Sam hurries the crew along, negatively impacting their work.

title: This Sand Is Your Sand
description: Wile E. Coyote hires The Looney Builders to build him a house in the desert so he can be alone. The Road Runner tries to pay him a visit causing Wile E. to heighten his security measures.

title: Sticky Feelings
description: Vivie gets angry when David accidentally takes her winning turn in a playground game. Barney helps Vivie process her anger, so she can work through it and keep playing with her friends.

title: Super Builders
description: The Looney Builders play superheroes and decide to upgrade their vehicles and headquarters. However, when one of Wile E. Coyote's inventions goes rogue, the crew must work together to save the day!

title: Squeaky Clean
description: The Looney Builders build their headquarters a car wash. Daffy doesn't want to wash Dumpy and goes to extreme lengths to keep him dirty and preserve their memories.

title: The Brave Little Tweety/Foghorn's Talkin' in the Barnyard (song)/Puddle Olympics
description: The Brave Little Tweety: Tweety takes a role in a play too seriously and begins to believe he's a real superhero./The Puddle Olympics: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

title: The Missing Valentine
description: When Barney notices that Vivie forgot to make a valentine for someone special on Valentine's Day, the kids embark on a magical quest to find out who it is. They complete challenges that help Vivie realize she forgot to make one for herself!

title: Silly Time
description: When Mel doesn't want to stop making a funny sound, Barney and the kids go on an adventure to the Waterverse to meet a clingy hermit crab named Hermie. Hermie helps Mel realize that there's a proper time and a place for certain behaviors.
